race.comment: CASINO SHOWGIRL (1) produced a nice effort here on debut beaten 0.9L lengths over this distance. Will have benefited from that experience and fitter is well-placed to go one better. HEAT OF THE NIGHT (4) has had two runs since the switch from a Victorian yard and is building towards her maiden success. Ran a solid race beaten 2.2L over 1350m at Strathalbyn, and will appreciate the step up in trip. She has plenty up her sleeve. GOOCHEE GAL (3) is racing better than the form line suggests. She was back on track beaten 2.2L in the CASINO SHOWGIRL race and her close-up effort at Swan Hill three back over a mile reads strongly. BLABBER MOUTH (9) needed the debut outing and no surprise to see her improve quickly up in distance for a leading yard. The gate is awkward, but the 2kg claim assists.
